    "recap_headline": "West Virginia University",
    "recap_text": "WACO, Texas \u2013\u00a0A dominant performance on the mound from redshirt junior\nMaxx Yehl\npaved the way for an 8-0 victory for the West Virginia University baseball team over Baylor, Sunday afternoon at Baylor Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 13-4 overall and 2-1 in the Big 12 while the Bears fall to 11-8 and 1-2 in conference play.\nYehl threw 8.0 scoreless innings and struck out 12 batters while walking just one and allowing three hits, all singles. It was the most strikeouts for a Mountaineer since\nGriffin Kirn\nstruck out 14 against Utah last season and the most by a WVU pitcher away from Morgantown since Ryan Bergert struck out 14 against St. Joseph's in 2020 in Myrtle Beach. It was also the most by a Mountaineer in a true road game since Alek Manoah struck out 13 against Kansas State in 2019.\nAt the plate, senior\nMatthew Graveline\nhit his team-leading fourth home run of the season and drove in two runs. Junior\nArmani Guzman\nhad two hits and two RBI while sophomore\nGavin Kelly\ncollected two hits to raise his average to .423.\nBaylor pitcher Ethan Calder matched zeroes with Yehl for the first five innings and faced the minimum until the sixth when Graveline greeted him with a solo home run to left, landing on the soccer field 404 feet away.\nIn the seventh, WVU added four runs, starting with a sacrifice fly by graduate student\nBrodie Kresser\n. A double by Guzman plated two more runs before a passed ball brought in the fourth run. The Mountaineers tacked on three more runs in the ninth on an error, a bases-loaded walk, and sacrifice fly by senior\nPaul Schoenfeld\n.\nFreshman\nDavid Perez\nstruck out the side in the ninth to close out WVU's third shutout of the season, matching the total from last season. Perez now has 13 strikeouts and zero walks in 7.0 innings of work.\nThe Mountaineers will be back in action on Tuesday evening when they host Penn State. First pitch from Kendrick Family Ballpark is set for 6:30 p.m.\nFor more information on the Mountaineers, follow @WVUBaseball on\nTwitter\n,\nFacebook\n, and\nInstagram\n."
  },
